    • createGame

      public static void createGame(int numberPlayers, int numberCommonGoalCards, int id, String nickname)
      Prints that a game has been created by a player, and prints its attributes. It synchronizes on System.out.
      Parameters:
      numberPlayers - The number of players that have to connect to start the game.
      numberCommonGoalCards - The number of CommonGoalCards in the game.
      id - The ID of the game created.
      nickname - The nickname of the player that has created the game.
